      {
        "content": "Social media companies routinely collect vast amounts of personal data beyond what is necessary for their services, often without explicit user consent or awareness. They use sophisticated algorithms to track, analyze, and monetize user behavior, creating detailed profiles that are sold to advertisers and sometimes exposed in data breaches. These practices infringe on privacy rights, as users are not fully informed or in control of how their information is used. Without strict regulations, social media platforms will continue exploiting user data, undermining individual privacy and autonomy in favor of profit.",
